  "text": "The HTTP connection manager route matching in Envoy is implemented across multiple layers:\n\n## HTTP Connection Manager Core\nThe main entry point is `ConnectionManagerImpl` in source/common/http/conn_manager_impl.h/cc. It manages incoming HTTP connections and coordinates request processing. The `ActiveStream` inner class handles per-stream state and calls `refreshCachedRoute()` method (conn_manager_impl.cc:1608) to perform route selection.\n\n## Route Selection Pipeline\nWhen `refreshCachedRoute()` is invoked, it calls the `route()` method on the snapped route configuration object (a `Router::Config` instance), which is obtained from the route config provider. This leads to `ConfigImpl::route()` (config_impl.cc:2312), the main route selection entry point.\n\n## Virtual Host Selection\n`ConfigImpl::route()` delegates to `RouteMatcher::route()` (config_impl.cc:2161), which first calls `RouteMatcher::findVirtualHost()` (config_impl.cc:2113) to select the appropriate virtual host based on request headers (like Host header). Virtual hosts are represented by the `VirtualHostImpl` class (config_impl.h:384).\n\n## Route Matching Algorithm\nOnce a virtual host is selected, the system performs route matching by calling `VirtualHostImpl::getRouteFromEntries()` (config_impl.cc:1978) or `VirtualHostImpl::getRouteFromRoutes()` (config_impl.cc:1941). These methods iterate through configured routes, each represented by implementations of the `RouteEntryImplBase` class (config_impl.h:639), which includes:\n- `PrefixRouteEntryImpl` - matches URL path prefixes\n- `PathRouteEntryImpl` - matches exact URL paths\n- `RegexRouteEntryImpl` - matches URL paths with regex patterns\n- `UriTemplateMatcherRouteEntryImpl` - matches URI templates\n- `ConnectRouteEntryImpl` - handles CONNECT method\n- `PathSeparatedPrefixRouteEntryImpl` - matches path-separated prefixes\n\nEach route entry implements the `Matchable` interface (config_impl.h:65) with its `matches()` method (config_impl.h:76) that compares request headers and stream info against the route's matching criteria.\n\n## Route Action Dispatch\nOnce a matching route is found, the `RouteEntry` interface provides methods to determine the cluster to route to via `clusterName()` (config_impl.cc:898), and provides access to route-specific actions through methods like `clusterNotFoundResponseCode()`, `timeoutPolicy()`, `retryPolicy()`, etc. defined in the Route interface.\n\n## Supporting Components\n- `Router` filter (source/common/router/router.h/cc) uses the selected route to forward requests to the appropriate upstream cluster\n- `ScopedRdsConfigProvider` (scoped_rds.h/cc) provides dynamic scoped route configuration support\n- `RdsConfigProvider` (rds_impl.h/cc) provides dynamic route configuration discovery\n- `HeaderParser` (header_parser.h/cc) handles header mutations specified in routes\n- HTTP Connection Manager extension in source/extensions/filters/network/http_connection_manager/ provides the filter factory configuration\n\nThe entire flow from incoming request to route selection happens synchronously in the connection manager, with route caching to avoid re-selection for requests that don't modify relevant headers."
}

